276
00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:18.000
But I don't want you to get distracted.

277
00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:20.000
I want Marinette to love me.

278
00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:22.000
And I want the magic.

279
00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:25.000
Take it or not.

280
00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:27.000
Okay, I'll take it.

281
00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:29.000
Happy birthday.

282
00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:32.000
Marinette.

283
00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:36.000
Thanks for accepting my invitation.

284
00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:38.000
Wow, this is beautiful.

285
00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:39.000
Do you like it?

286
00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:41.000
Wait, I'm just getting started.

287
00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:48.000
Come on, this has to be a joke.

288
00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:49.000
Huh?

289
00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:52.000
Sorry, I didn't want to scare you.

290
00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:55.000
I just can't draw properly in the dark.

291
00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:56.000
Hmm.

292
00:12:56.000 --> 00:12:58.000
Voila!

293
00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:06.000
Huh?

294
00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:10.000
You're so talented.

295
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:13.000
I don't understand why you use your power to harm people.

296
00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:14.000
Not everyone.

297
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.000
Only Chloe.

298
00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:17.000
And I'm not going to do this again.

299
00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:18.000
You finally kept your word.

300
00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:20.000
I'm going to keep my word, too.

301
00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:31.000
I'm actually drawing a little bit.

302
00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:32.000
I'm not as good as you, of course.

303
00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:34.000
I'm sure you're a great artist.

304
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:38.000
Can I draw something special for your birthday, please?

305
00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:43.000
That would be great.

306
00:13:43.000 --> 00:13:48.000
Marinette, give me my pen back.

307
00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:49.000
I need to draw something.

308
00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:50.000
Now.

309
00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:52.000
No, this will stay with me.

310
00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:54.000
Black cat, now!

311
00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:58.000
Marinette, did you become one with him?

312
00:13:58.000 --> 00:13:59.000
You deceived me.

313
00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:01.000
I thought you liked me.

314
00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:03.000
But you're just like Chloe.

315
00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:05.000
You're messing with me.

316
00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:07.000
Come on, are you serious?

317
00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:10.000
Why is everyone comparing me to Chloe tonight?

318
00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:24.000
And I'm taking my word back.

319
00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:27.000
Chloe will have a lesson she'll never forget.

320
00:14:27.000 --> 00:14:33.000
We're stuck.

321
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:34.000
Really.

322
00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:39.000
Black cat, put your stick like this.

323
00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:40.000
Then stretch it out, okay?

324
00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:41.000
Good idea.

325
00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:43.000
Yeah, I'm good.

326
00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:49.000
I have to go.

327
00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:50.000
Superhero never ends.

328
00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:51.000
Women in need of help.

329
00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:52.000
Waiting girls.

330
00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:53.000
There are many people to save.

331
00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:55.000
You can thank me later.

332
00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:58.000
Am I going to thank you?

333
00:14:58.000 --> 00:14:59.000
He should thank me.

334
00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:01.000
If I hadn't told him how to do his job,

335
00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:03.000
we would still be there.

336
00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:05.000
While the word is out.

337
00:15:05.000 --> 00:15:07.000
We have to help to save Chloe.

338
00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:13.000
I'm so sorry, teacher.

339
00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:15.000
I couldn't work on my project

340
00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:17.000
after what happened in the library.

341
00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:19.000
It was so traumatic.

342
00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:21.000
Think about what you did to my hair.

343
00:15:21.000 --> 00:15:25.000
Come on.

344
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:27.000
Who would believe that an idiot

345
00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:28.000
can never make me look ugly

346
00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:30.000
with even a hair dryer?

347
00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:35.000
Black cat, is that you?

348
00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:41.000
Chloe.

349
00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:43.000
Where are you?

350
00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:44.000
Are you hiding?

351
00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:46.000
This is so cute.

352
00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:48.000
You're playing hide and seek.

353
00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:50.000
In the closet?

354
00:15:50.000 --> 00:16:00.000
I won, Chloe.

355
00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:01.000
I found you.

356
00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:04.000
My Schnell dresses.

357
00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:05.000
My bling bling shoes.

358
00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:07.000
You're a monster.

359
00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:09.000
You like to mess with people.

360
00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:11.000
But when someone else messes with you,

361
00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:12.000
you don't like it.

362
00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:13.000
Don't you, Chloe?

363
00:16:13.000 --> 00:16:14.000
Don't you?

364
00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:22.000
Your shoe is broken.

365
00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:23.000
Watch your wrists.

366
00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:24.000
Wow.

367
00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:25.000
Look what your cat brought.

368
00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:27.000
Black cat can't take me anywhere.

369
00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:29.000
I came on my own.

370
00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:31.000
What was this secret mission?

371
00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:32.000
If I told you,

372
00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:33.000
it wouldn't be a secret.

373
00:16:33.000 --> 00:16:34.000
In comic books,

374
00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:36.000
this is called the last fight.

375
00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:37.000
The thing is,

376
00:16:37.000 --> 00:16:38.000
if you knew it,

377
00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:39.000
you wouldn't waste a drop of blood

378
00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:40.000
to save it.

379
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:42.000
That's the worst part.

380
00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:43.000
That's not true.

381
00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:45.000
Everyone loves me.

382
00:16:45.000 --> 00:16:49.000
Watch out.

384
00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:11.000
Oh, light.

385
00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:12.000
Black cat.

386
00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:13.000
It can't draw in the dark.

387
00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:14.000
I got it.

388
00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:17.000
Cat's Claw.

389
00:17:17.000 --> 00:17:28.000
Take it, cat.

390
00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:29.000
Play with the flang.

391
00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:31.000
Hey.

392
00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:01.000
Jumping ball?

393
00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:03.000
Try to stop me with it,

394
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:04.000
little lady.

395
00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:05.000
[laughs]

396
00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:10.000
Nice to meet you.

397
00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:28.000
Oh, hurry up.

398
00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:34.000
[speaking Turkish]

399
00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:39.000
[speaking Turkish]

400
00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:44.000
[speaking Turkish]

401
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:46.000
[speaking Turkish]

402
00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:49.000
[speaking Turkish]

403
00:18:49.000 --> 00:18:58.000
Where am I?

404
00:18:58.000 --> 00:19:00.000
- Let's check it out. - Let's check it out.

405
00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:02.000
No!

406
00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:04.000
That miracle was mine.

407
00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:06.000
And it was going to happen.

408
00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:09.000
When I get them all, I'm going to rule the world.

409
00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:11.000
Finally.

410
00:19:11.000 --> 00:19:17.000
What happened when the owl and the black cat came to the scene?

411
00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:20.000
Well, to be honest, they did worse.

412
00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:23.000
They just got lost and started to break everything.

413
00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:25.000
They threw plastic balls in my room.

414
00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:26.000
Plastic balls?

415
00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:30.000
I hope you had a good time doing that important thing last night.

416
00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:32.000
I'm so sorry, Sabrina.

417
00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:35.000
We can meet at the library today and work on the project.

418
00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:36.000
- What do you say? - It's too late.

419
00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:38.000
Chloe and I will do the project together.

420
00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:41.000
- So, are you going to do the project? - Of course.

421
00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:43.000
I mean, after all the things we've been through.

422
00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:45.000
This is a nice hat.

423
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:48.000
I know, right? Chloe gave it to me.

424
00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:50.000
He's my real buddy.

425
00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:53.000
Chloe, your geography homework is ready.

426
00:19:55.000 --> 00:19:56.000
Hello.

427
00:19:56.000 --> 00:19:58.000
I heard your adventure with the black cat yesterday.

428
00:19:58.000 --> 00:19:59.000
Were you scared?

429
00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:01.000
Me? Scared?

430
00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:02.000
It was like a dream.

431
00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:03.000
I mean, you're a dream.

432
00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:05.000
I mean, I wanted to say you could see in your dream.

433
00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:07.000
Oh, this must be a nightmare.

434
00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:08.000
Okay.

435
00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:10.000
So, what do you think about the black cat?

436
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.000
Isn't she great?

437
00:20:11.000 --> 00:20:12.000
I mean, of course.

438
00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:14.000
Yes, but she's not as great as you.

439
00:20:14.000 --> 00:20:15.000
Who could it be anyway?

440
00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:17.000
You're the best, right?

441
00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:19.000
So, is this yes?

442
00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:28.000
You just realized how great Adriana is, right?

443
00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:29.000
It touched my shoulder.

444
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:31.000
I'm never going to wash this jacket again.

445
00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:35.000
Honey, I think you should control your emotions better.